.TH "rio_lock_device" 9 "rio_lock_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rio_lock_device \- Acquires host device lock for specified device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rio_lock_device
.BI "(struct rio_mport *port "  ","
.BI "u16 destid "  ","
.BI "u8 hopcount "  ","
.BI "int wait_ms "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
Master port to send transaction
.IP "destid" 12
Destination ID for device/switch
.IP "hopcount" 12
Hopcount to reach switch
.IP "wait_ms" 12
Max wait time in msec (0 = no timeout)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Attepts to acquire host device lock for specified device
Returns 0 if device lock acquired or EINVAL if timeout expires.
